CatDescriptText: Raymond Kemp was the second African American to play n the NFL and was the last known living player from the Pittsburgh Steelers 1933 team originally called the Pittsburgh Pirates.
TitMainTitle: Raymond Kemp seated on table with certificate reading "Duquesne University proudly enrolls Raymond H. Kemp, Sports Hall of Fame", with plaques on wall behind awarded to Ray Kemp, coach of 1960 Olympic Stars track team, and others
